description:
&lt;p&gt;X-Ray Department, 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Office Hours are from 8am until 7pm, you will be required to work until 7pm once a week on a rolling rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rotational Saturday shift is also required (approximately 1 in 6)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in working as part of a team to provide a full clerical service to the x-ray department? This will involve receptioning patients-booking them onto the departmental computer system, filing and making appointments as well as acting as a clerical coordinator in our CT control room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the X-Ray Department it is how you go about your duties that matters to us. You should be enthusiastic, self motivated and have excellent communication skills to be able to work well with all levels of staff and members of the public. Full training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexibility in hours worked will be necessary to cover annual leave/sickness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLaura BeardshawJob titleRadiology Administration Manager - Weston SiteEmail addresslaura.beardshaw@nhs.netTelephone number01934 881016Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Beardshaw 01934 881016&lt;/p&gt;
